Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @Premium Tomato Mix{125%g}.

Pop the tomatoes onto a medium #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil and the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until they're softened and starting to burst, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @Cannellini Beans{1%tin}.

== Pesto Bulgur ==

Pour the @Boiled Water for the Bulgur{240%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} on high heat, then stir in the @Bulgur Wheat{120%g} and half the @Vegetable Stock Paste{20%g}.

Bring back to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Put a lid on the saucepan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{}. Once hot, add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Tomato Passata{1%tin}, cannellini beans, @Mixed Herbs{1%tsp}, remaining vegetable stock paste and the @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer.

Simmer the sauce until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

== Finishing ==

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the frying pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Butter{10%g} until melted.

Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

When the bulgur is ready, fluff up the grains with a #fork{} and stir through the @Fresh Pesto{32%g}.

Share your pesto bulgur between your #bowls{}.

Top with the cannellini bean stew and spoon over roasted balsamic tomatoes.

Finish by crumbling over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%g}.

Enjoy!